## Structural Questions

{Questions about the object's design, schema, or ETL that cannot be answered from code alone}

## Tier 5 Re-Review Needed

> Tier 5 (domain expert) overrides whose underlying Tier 1–3 source has materially changed
> since the correction was made. The Tier 5 is still applied, but a domain expert should
> confirm it remains valid given the new upstream definition.

| Column | Tier 5 Correction | Was Based On (old Tier 1–3) | New Tier 1–3 | Change Summary |
|--------|-------------------|----------------------------|--------------|----------------|
```

On **rerun** (full or review-rerun): If a previous `.review-needed.md` exists, read `## Reviewer Corrections` first.
Apply all entries as Tier 5 overrides. In the new sidecar, carry resolved corrections forward
with `[RESOLVED]` prefix in the "Current (wrong)" column. Remove resolved items from
Tier 4 / Clarification sections. **Staleness check**: For each Tier 5, compare the "Current
(wrong)" column (the old Tier 1–3 text the correction was based on) against the freshly
generated Tier 1–3 description. If the Tier 1–3 has materially changed (not just formatting),
populate the `## Tier 5 Re-Review Needed` section and tag the column `(Tier 5 — domain expert, RE-REVIEW)`.
Once a reviewer confirms the Tier 5 still holds, they update the "Current (wrong)" column to
match the new Tier 1–3, clearing the staleness flag on the next run.

**Review-rerun mode**: When triggered by the review-rerun scope (not a full pipeline run), Phase 11
uses the previously gathered phase data (Phases 1–10 are NOT re-run). Only the documentation
generation and ALTER deployment are refreshed. This makes review-rerun fast (~2-3 min per table).

